        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 17 at 8:53PM CDT by NWS Quad Cities IA IL</headline>
        <description>At 853 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Charlotte, or 11 miles northwest of Clinton, moving north at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could cause minor tree limb damage and blow
around unsecured objects.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Preston around 900 PM CDT.
Miles around 905 PM CDT.

Other locations in the path of this storm include Spragueville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
